    {
      "index": 1,
      "label": "REVEAL",
      "text": "And no, it's not the ocean \u2014 that's the internet's favorite wrong answer. It's the air itself: sunlight collides with nitrogen and oxygen molecules a thousand times smaller than a wavelength of light, scatters in every direction... but short wavelengths scatter way harder, following an inverse-fourth-power rule. Blue bounces around the atmosphere five to ten times more than red.",
      "overlay": "1/\u03bb\u2074",
      "speaker": null,
