    {
      "index": 2,
      "label": "DETAIL",
      "text": "Here's the kicker: violet actually scatters the MOST, so the violet-sky paradox is completely real. Three things save us from purple skies \u2014 the sun emits less violet to begin with, ozone absorbs a chunk before it reaches us, and your eyes are genuinely terrible at violet, so the scattered mix your brain reads comes out blue.",
      "overlay": "3 Reasons",
      "speaker": null,
